# ==============================================================================
# Claude Code Configuration - .gitignore
# ==============================================================================
# This file prevents sensitive session data from being committed to git.
# Only share configuration files and documentation, never session history.

# ==============================================================================
# SESSION AND CONVERSATION DATA
# ==============================================================================
# projects/ - Contains full conversation transcripts in JSONL format
# WHY HIDDEN: Includes all code snippets, file paths, project names, and
# conversations that may contain proprietary code, API keys, or sensitive
# business logic from your actual development projects.
projects/

# history.jsonl - Global conversation history across all sessions
# WHY HIDDEN: Complete record of all interactions with Claude Code, may
# contain sensitive queries, code, or debugging information.
history.jsonl

# ==============================================================================
# FILE HISTORY AND VERSIONS
# ==============================================================================
# file-history/ - Snapshots of files at different versions during editing
# WHY HIDDEN: Contains actual source code from your projects that was edited
# during Claude Code sessions. This is YOUR code and should not be shared.
file-history/

# ==============================================================================
# DEBUG AND LOGGING
# ==============================================================================
# debug/ - Debug logs and error traces
# WHY HIDDEN: May contain stack traces, error messages, file paths, and other
# debugging information that could expose project structure or issues.
debug/

# ==============================================================================
# TASK MANAGEMENT
# ==============================================================================
# todos/ - Task lists created during sessions
# WHY HIDDEN: Contains project-specific task lists that may reference
# proprietary features, bugs, or implementation details.
todos/

# ==============================================================================
# SHELL HISTORY
# ==============================================================================
# shell-snapshots/ - Snapshots of shell commands executed during sessions
# WHY HIDDEN: May contain sensitive commands, file paths, environment variables,
# API tokens, or other credentials used in development.
shell-snapshots/

# ==============================================================================
# IDE STATE
# ==============================================================================
# ide/ - IDE lock files and state information
# WHY HIDDEN: Contains temporary state and lock files that are machine-specific
# and not useful for sharing.
ide/

# ==============================================================================
# TELEMETRY AND ANALYTICS
# ==============================================================================
# statsig/ - Telemetry and usage analytics data
# WHY HIDDEN: Contains usage statistics and analytics that are specific to
# your individual usage patterns.
statsig/

# ==============================================================================
# NOTE: agents/ is NOT ignored here because this is the distribution package
# User's personal agents will be in ~/.claude/agents/
# See .claude/.gitignore for protecting personal agents in user installs

# ==============================================================================
# EDITOR WORKSPACE
# ==============================================================================
# .vscode/ - VS Code workspace settings
# WHY HIDDEN: Personal editor preferences and workspace configurations that
# are machine-specific.
.vscode/

# ==============================================================================
# KEEP THESE FILES (They are safe and useful to share!)
# ==============================================================================
# !commands/ - Custom slash commands (kept)
# !*.md - Documentation files like README.md, CUSTOM_COMMANDS.md, etc. (kept)
# These contain reusable configurations that help other developers.
